Name: samuel kwablah tamatey
Details: on march 17 1995, joseph ewudzi woode was gunned down by samuel kwablah tamatey as he left his residence in etobicoke, ontario. tamatey is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for first degree murder. he is believed to be hiding in his native country ghana.

Name: george armour
Alias: gordon gregg armour /  donald armour /  george lyln britt /  george liebers /  donald jay david scott /  david anderson /  don anderson /  gary t jordan /  james theodore oliver /  jim oliver
Details: in 1989, george armour was sentenced to 2 years for false pretences, forged documents and failing to comply. while on parole, armour left canada and fled to south america and to the united states. armour has been employed in a variety of jobs both in south america and in the united states.

Name: andre fernando riquelme
Details: andre fernando riquelme was involved in a fight that broke out in the west end of toronto, resulting in three individuals being shot, one of whom did not survive. riquelme is wanted for first degree murder and two counts of attempted murder in relation to this event.

Name: rie ikeda
Alias: rie ikeda davidovitch /  rie ikeda- davidovitch
Details: on november 29 2003, rie ikeda took her son to japan and never returned to canada.

Name: conor vincent d'monte
Alias: brian black /  manuel nico ortega /  benzo / " b"
Details: conor d'monte is believed to be a high ranking member of the united nations gang. he is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for the slaying of rival gang member kevin leclair. d'monte is also wanted for the conspiracy to murder the bacon brothers and/or their associates. d'monte is known to frequent vancouver, edmonton, calgary, toronto and montreal canada. he is also known to travel to spain and asia. conor d'monte is associated to a drug network in mexico and he was last seen in the vancouver area in january 2011.

Name: mieczyslaw (mike) widziak
Details: mike widziak began sexually assaulting his daughter at the age of 13. this behaviour continued for the next 3 years progressing further and becoming more violent until police were made aware. widziak was arrested but has failed to appear for these charges and it is unknown where he is. mike widziak is originally from poland and regularly made visits.

Name: peng victor li
Details: peng victor li is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for first degree murder in connection to a beating death of a markham ontario teenager. li has connections in british columbia and in china and is believed to be using a passport in his alias name: hao lu.

Name: nasir ameeriar
Details: take no action to apprehend this person yourself. report any information to the nearest rcmp detachment or the police in your area or contact crime stoppers at 1-800-222-8477.

Name: charles peter billone
Details: charles billone sexually assaulted his 9 year old stepdaughter for approximately 3 years, stopping only after his daughter spoke to police. he is also believed to have committed further sexual assaults against his step daughter's friend. billone was arrested on this matter but was released prior to attending court. billone never returned to attend court and is currently wanted on a canada-wide warrant for sexual assault, sexual interference and fail to attend court.

Name: mario ruben gonzalez
Details: wanted for the abduction of his son, alex gonzales. alex was abducted on august 23 1991.

Name: luo li shi
Charges: possession of a controlled substance for purpose of traffickingproduction of a controlled substance
Details: on july 15 2010, while executing a search warrant at a residence in new brunswick, police discovered a large scale marihuana grow operation where over 1,600 marihuana plants were seized. luo li shi was the only occupant of the residence. he was held in custody but released on bail on july 22 2010 and is currently wanted on a canada-wide warrant. shi is a chinese citizen and canada border services agency has also issued a canada-wide warrant for his arrest. shi's last know address was in scarborough ontario.

Name: savang sychantha
Details: on april 22 2002, savang sychantha and an accomplice beat a male victim to death and disposed of the body in a bush lot. the police investigation revealed that sychantha was involved in the illicit drug trade and the victim was in financial debt to the suspect. sychantha fled to asia following this offence but it is believed that he may have returned to canada and is potentially living under an assumed name and identity.

Name: gregory allan pictou
Details: on february 21 1981, a subject by the name of john gleason was found in the state of mummified decomposition in the basement of a local building in ottawa. an autopsy revealed that the subject had been stabbed approximately 50 times in the front and back torso and had his throat slit from ear to ear. after further investigation into the murder, it was revealed that gregory pictou was a primary assailant in the attack on gleason. a canada-wide warrant was issued for his arrest for murder.

Name: john alan joseph tucsok
Details: john alan joseph tucsok is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for multiple sex offences involving female youths. tucsok was a church elder in ontario and sexually assaulted female youths associated with the church over a 4 year period. he may still be a member of, or associating with christian groups. tucsok was at large on bail when he fled ontario in 2003. he was last known to be in the calgary area.

Name: richard gleeson
Details: richard gleeson served a six year sentence for manslaughter that he committed in 1995. he has been wanted on a canada-wide warrant for parole violation since 2000.

Name: edgard elias
Details: in november 1991, edgard elias entered a convenience store armed with a handgun and robbed the store clerk. when the store clerk made a motion towards the counter, elias shot the victim in the head and abdomen. elias turned and pointed the gun at another employee, then ran from the store. the victim was deceased when police arrived. elias was later identified as the accused and has an outstanding canada-wide warrant for his arrest.

Name: ralph duval
Charges: conspiracy to import/export a controlled substancedrug offences
Details: ralph duval is wanted in connection with projet colisée, an international investigation project established to destabilize organized crime and more specifically, the rizzuto clan. this significant investigation, which took place between 2002 and 2006 was conducted by the unité mixte d'enquête sur le crime organisé (umeco), an rcmp initiative composed of several law enforcement agencies.

Name: kevin louis vermette
Details: reward : $25,000

Name: jose de jesus kratc-usman
Charges: conspiracy to import/export a controlled substance
Details: a sixteen month undercover operation was conducted in the greater toronto area from july 1996 to october 1997. the case was a joint effort between the rcmp and peel regional police. the operation culminated in the seizure of three hundred kilograms of cocaine valued at 90 million dollars. it was the largest seizure ever in the region of peel. it severely disrupted a cell of colombian based traffickers, three of whom have already pleaded guilty. kratc-usman was a high ranking representative of a cocaine organization in south america. he was in canada to evaluate the canadian operation and gave the final approval before the traffickers attempted to smuggle in the cocaine. the rcmp consider kratc-usman to be among the very upper echelon of international cocaine traffickers.

Name: abdoulkadi ali musse
Alias: abdoulkadi musse /  abdoulkadi ali musse /  abdoulkadir ali musse /  abdi abdul kadir mousse
Details: on august 24 1994, nellie bobbish was found dead in a montréal home that she occupied with her boyfriend abdoulkadi ali musse. the victim had been stabbed several times. musse was seen leaving the premises. abdoulkadi ali musse is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for second degree murder.

Name: abdi aliow elmi
Details: on october 18 1991, abdi aliow elmi conned a 20 year old female into going to his apartment where he brutally beat and sexually assaulted her. elmi was arrested and released on a recognizance before the court. he breached his recognizance and a canada-wide warrant has been issued for his arrest.

Name: mohamud abukar hagi
Details: after a sidewalk altercation, mohamud abukar hagi shot and killed his victim and fled the scene. the firearm was recovered and an investigation identified hagi as the accused. a canada-wide warrant was issued for hagis arrest. he has been sighted in toronto and windsor, ontario, but he remains at large. hagi has access to firearms.

Name: michel abbaudi estephan
Details: on september 4 2003, an associate of michel abbaudi estephan's was attacked and killed by several male suspects at an arcade in ottawa. estephan responded by shooting at the subjects with a handgun. he was apprehended by police and charged with attempted murder and numerous other charges. estephan fled after being released from custody on bail.

Name: naser akbarian
Details: wanted for the 1996 parental abduction of his daughter, nina akbarian. believed to be in iran.

Name: sawaran singh sekhon
Details: sawaran singh sekhon is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for the shooting death of devinder singh gill that occurred in the early hours of friday, september 11 2009 in brampton ontario. sekhon may have fled to the area of gilla (ludhiana) in india.

Name: abdikarim ismail ashoor
Alias: anwar ismail abdalle /  abdikarim ismal ashoor
Details: on march 4 2000, ashoor was working as a taxi driver in fort mcmurray alberta when he allegedly sexually assaulted a young woman. ashoor was arrested and released on bail, but then failed to attend court and fled the jurisdiction.

Name: emmanuel eliezer mardochee feuerwerker
Details: on april 29, 2011, the ontario superior court convicted emmanuel feuerwerker under the criminal code of canada for fraud over $5000 section 380(1)(a), possession of property obtained by crime section 354(1) and laundering proceeds of crime section 462.31(a). as of july 15, 2011, feuerwerker has failed to appear in court for his sentencing and he is now wanted canada wide. feuerwerker has connections with other fraudsters in the toronto area.

Name: ronald jeffrey bax
Details: in cooperation with the fbi

Name: kin chuen tommy ho
Details: kin chuen tommy ho was serving an 18 year sentence for drug import and trafficking offences. ho was released on parole in 2005 and was meeting his release conditions until he absconded in 2006. he is believed to have connections in china, hong kong and australia.

Name: hossein ghoodjani
Details: on october 24 1993, hossein ghoodjani called 9-1-1 from his home in toronto and told the police communications operator that he had killed his wife with a rope. police officers attending the scene met ghoodjani at the door and found dorys delgadillo unconscious and not breathing. emergency medical services and fire department personnel managed to revive the victim but she died in hospital later that day. hossein ghoodjani was charged with first degree murder. the accused absconded during the preliminary hearing and is currently wanted on a canada-wide warrant.

Name: norman washington needham
Details: on march 10 1993, norman needham shot and killed dave sylvester francis. the victims body was dumped over the guardrail of a highway on-ramp and was discovered three weeks later. in april 1993, an arrest warrant was issued charging norman needham with manslaughter. he is believed to have fled to jamaica.

Name: hossein marejnejad
Alias: marejnejad hossein /  hoseein marej nejad /  john marejnejad
Charges: invitation to sexual touchingsexual assaultsexual offences
Details: hossein marejnejad was born in iran. he previously worked at and owned a convenience store and an iranian restaurant. he was possibly spotted in auckland new zealand and seen in tonga (south pacific).

Name: sergius joseph maher
Details: sergius joseph maher was serving a six year sentence for manslaughter. he breached his parole and has been wanted on a canada-wide warrant since 1982.

Name: guido hans joachim metzger
Details: guido hans joachim metzger is alleged to have committed sexual assaults against young people who were known to him in the late 1970s. metzger failed to attend court in 1988. a canada-wide warrant was issued for failing to appear and two counts of indecent assault. police information indicates that he may have fled to guyana.

Name: tan tieu hong
Details: on january 31 1994, tan tieu hong had an altercation with a waiter at a toronto restaurant, at which time hong threatened to kill the waiter. hong left the restaurant but returned later that night armed with a handgun. hong shot his victim, leaving him paralyzed from the waist down. tan tieu hong is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for attempted murder.

Name: ali omer mohamed
Details: in the early morning of january 18th, 2018, the victim attended a residential apartment to socialize with persons he knew. at approximately 3 am, the accused, ali omer mohamed attended the same apartment and started drinking with the victim. just before 6 am, mohamed and the victim became embroiled in an argument which led to the accused shooting the victim. the victim sustained a fatal gunshot to the torso. subsequent to investigation, mohamed was charged with second degree murder and a warrant was issued for his arrest. it is believed that on or around january 23rd, 2018, the accused fled canada to djibouti and may have travelled to somalia or ethiopia.

Name: mohsen dadgar-kiani
Alias: mohsen amir dadgar- kiani /  mohsen dadgar kiani /  mohsen dadger- kiai
Details: mohsen dadgar-kiani has been charged with numerous criminal offences against his ex-wife but was permitted supervised visits with their two children. on may 20 1996, dadgar-kiani took his daughter to a shopping mall in ottawa ontario and from there proceeded with a well planned escape route and managed to flee to iran. the daughter has since been returned to canada. moshen dadgar-kiani is still wanted on a canada-wide warrant for parental abduction and several other criminal offences.

Name: vaclav roman starostik
Alias: roman vaclav starostik /  ronan vaclav starostik /  vaclav roman starstik
Details: vaclav roman starostik was the head of one of the worlds largest trafficking organizations. he was serving a life sentence for conspiracy to traffic heroin and was on parole when he absconded in 2004. starostik has access money from the proceeds of crime. he was last known to be in czech republic.

Name: brian joseph mcconnell
Alias: john scott henderson /  brian joseph mc connell
Details: mcconnell is serving a two year, seven month sentence for production of a controlled substance. his current status is listed as suspended ual.

Name: claudio dimatteo
Alias: claudio di metteo /  claudio d imatto
Details: claudio dimatteo has a history of drug and fraud charges from the mid-1970s to early 1980s. in 1984 he was released from jail and was under mandatory supervision while living and working in toronto, ontario. dimatteo disappeared in 1985.

Name: wissam tarabichi
Details: on april 4, 2018 the abbotsford police engaged in an investigation of parental abduction. investigators discovered that on march 24, 2018 wissam tarabichi took his two children, daughter aged 9 yrs and son aged 8 yrs, to seattle wa, usa. all three crossed the canadian/usa border near abbotsford bc. the following day tarabichi and his children boarded a plane in seattle and flew to beirut lebanon. as a result of the investigation tarabichi was charged with abduction in contravention of a custody order, section 282 ccc.

Name: bing jie ma
Details: on october 14 2008, ma sexually assaulted a woman at his residence. when she attempted to escape he choked her until she lost consciousness. it is believed that ma may have fled to eastern canada.

Name: tedroy anthony richardo davis
Alias: christian paul landeta /  anthony davies tedroy /  tedroy anthony richardo /  christian pacel ladeta
Details: tedroy davis' criminal convictions include robbery, weapon offences and aggravated assault. he served jail time for these offences and absconded while on parole.

Name: jean yves tremblay
Details: jean yves tremblay, along with 25 other accomplices, is a suspect in a multiple murder that occurred in lennoxville, quebec in 1985 when five members of the hells angels were murdered.

Name: varaporn gop toassami
Details: on november 18 2010, varaporn toassami departed vancouver with her daughter chonticha galame ellefson-toassami, and flew to bangkok, thailand. varaporn toassami has failed to return to canada with her daughter.

Name: marko anicic
Details: marko anicic was serving a five year sentence for carrying a concealed weapon, possession of a prohibited weapon and trafficking in a narcotic. anicic was granted an unescorted temporary absence permit to visit his family in toronto but failed to return.

Name: vijayaraja manickavasagar
Alias: vijay manickavasagar /  vijay manickavaragar /  vijayarajah manickavasagar /  vijayarajah prabakaran /  vijayaraja rantham /  bullet
Details: on march 20 2004, amretta singh was shot to death after returning home from a brampton night club. she was shot in retaliation for a dispute that occured between her brother and two male suspects at the night club. the investigation identified vijayaraja manickavasagar as the shooter and a canada-wide warrant was issued for his arrest. police believe manickavasagar may have traveled to sri lanka under a false passport.

Name: satheesan shanmugarajah
Details: following "projet chapitre" targeting a criminal organization specializing in cloning and distributing forged credit cards, satheesan shanmugarajah is presently wanted for conspiracy (5 counts), fraud over $5000 (3 counts), possession of instrument for copying credit card data (3 counts), forging or falsifying credit cards, commission of an offence for a criminal organization and participation in activities of a criminal organization.

Name: joanna catharina van bijsterveld
Alias: joanna vanbijsterveld /  johanna van bysterveld /  johanna vanbysterveld
Details: on march 18 2005, joanna catharina van bijsterveld abducted her daughter maria rosa di valerio. van bijsterveld does not have custody of the child.

Name: roxanne eliana yanez parada
Details: roxanne eliana yanez parada and her son jadon alexander yanez parada left canada to visit relatives in chile and did not return. the child's father has full custody and canadian courts have ordered that the child be returned. roxanne yanez parada is believed to be in chile.

Name: ashor sadeth shleimon
Alias: ashor sadeh shleimon /  shur sadeh shalemon
Details: ashor sadeth shleimon is known to have participated in two robberies and was sentenced to over 6 years in jail. less than a year after his release from prison, he breached his parole and has not been seen since.

Name: jacek ludwik pyszniak
Details: while impersonating a police officer, jacek ludwik pyszniak tricked his victim into exiting his vehicle. once the victim was outside the vehicle pyszniak shot him four times. he was charged with attempted murder and ordered to stand trial. pyszniak went missing a few days prior to the start of his trial. he is still at large.

Name: fei wing tsang
Details: fei wing tsang is wanted for four counts of assault with a weapon, four counts of forcible confinement and three counts of kidnapping in 1995.

Name: sexual assault suspect
Details: on july 12 2009, at approximately 3am, a woman in her mid 20s was walking alone and talking on her cell phone on squirrel street in banff, alberta. she was approached from behind by a male who tapped her on the shoulder. the male smashed her cell phone and suddenly threw her to the ground and sexually assaulted her. she screamed and fought back, scratching at the mans face and gouging his eyes. he punched her four times in the face and head before running away.

Name: elzbieta nowacki
Details: in april 2011, both parents traveled with their son aleksander to visit the mother's family in poland. the father returned to canada on his own may 13 2011. the mother, elzbieta nowacki and child did not return to canada. nowacki is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for abduction.

Name: henry stanley morales
Details: on july 13 2006, police responded to a call at a residential apartment and discovered the victim malena morales, deceased with obvious signs of trauma to the body. a canada-wide warrant was issued for her husband henry stanley morales. the accused is believed to have fled the country to mexico and may have since escaped to ecuador, guatemala, panama, el salvador or the southern united states (texas).

Name: abdiquadir hosh dirie
Details: wanted on a canada-wide warrant for sexual assault and extortion.

Name: edyta watkins
Details: on april 2 2009, a canada-wide warrant was issued for edyta watkins for the abduction of her two children, alexander and christopher watkins. investigation has revealed that the mother took the children to the united states where they boarded a plane and flew to germany. edyta watkins has connections in poland, germany, austria, czech republic and the united states. she and the children are believed to be in poland.

Name: kam cheung fung
Details: kam cheung fung was serving a fourteen year sentence for conspiracy to traffic narcotics. while on an escorted leave permit, fung escaped from the escorting correctional officer.

Name: suk woon lee
Details: suk woon lee's original offence is second degree murder. he was facing deportation to korea at the time of his absconment. on march 10 1990, lee's wife drove the subject to the airport. she was under the impression he was traveling to bangkok, thailand, however his whereabouts remain unknown. lee has a political science degree and is believed to be employed as a minister.

Name: david macdonald carroll
Details: david carroll is a known member of the hells angels criminal organization.

Name: jeffrey paul emery
Details: on april 13 2004, during a domestic argument with his common-law wife, jeffrey paul emery poured a bottle of hairspray over her then set her on fire. she suffered third-degree burns to her legs, torso, arms and face and much of her hair was burned away. emery refused to take her to the hospital. north vancouver rcmp were alerted to the incident more than a month later when a relative contacted police. emery was arrested, but absconded in december 2004 during an adjournment of his court case. he was convicted in absentia of aggravated assault and a canada-wide warrant was issued for his arrest.

Name: lisa santana
Details: lisa santana is wanted for second degree murder. she is known to be violent so caution is urged when approaching subject. she is believed to be in mexico.

Name: morteza izadifar
Details: on february 25 2005, richmond rcmp were made aware of a local limousine driver, morteza izadifar who was luring at risk teenagers by providing them with free limousine rides, cash and alcohol. he often entertained these youths in his vancouver apartment and engaged in inappropriate sexual activities. it is estimated that these assaults occurred between 1999-2002. izadifar is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for sexual assault and sexual interference with a person under 14. police believe he may have returned to the middle east, possibly iran.

Name: romana dittrichova
Details: on june 4 2005, romana dittrichova contravened a custody order when she travelled to the czech republic with her three children: adam dittrich, ludvik dittrich and robert dittrich.

Name: chieko teton
Details: chieko teton was with her husband henrik and their one year old son takaya in 2013 on vacation in yokohama, japan.

Name: ferid ahmed imam
Details: ferid ahmed imam is a former student of biochemistry at the university of manitoba. he was considered to be a well liked and respected member of the community and had no involvement in criminal activity prior to leaving canada. in march 2007, imam departed canada for pakistan where he became involved as a weapons instructor at a terrorist training camp aligned with al qaida. according to rcmp interviews, imam was positively identified as an al qaida weapons instructor using the alias "yousef". an rcmp witness interview showed that imam's objective in joining a terrorist organization and obtaining weapons training was to fight and kill nato soldiers in afghanistan. he was last seen in the town of miran shah, pakistan.

Name: robert donald joseph armstrong
Details: robert donald joseph armstrong has a history of assault, narcotics possessions and assaults on peace officers. he is presently wanted for escaping custody while being held on a charge of murder. his previous occupations include automobile purchasing agent, photographer and labourer.

Name: john douglas maguire
Details: wanted for commission of offence for terrorist group x2, conspiracy, participation in activity of terrorist group x2 and facilitating terrorist activity.

Name: george balgobin
Details: george balgobin was arrested in 1998 in toronto, ontario for importing narcotics. he served federal jail time before being released on parole, at which time he fled. balgobin was born in guyana, south america and has family in canada.

Name: neon daneyon jemmott
Details: on september 9 2005, neon daneyon jemmott and an accomplice attempted to rob two men during a drug transaction in a toronto area apartment. the victims were both shot during this altercation, one was fatally wounded. the surviving victim assisted police in identifying the suspects. one suspect was apprehended by police. neon daneyon jemmott remains at large and is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for first degree murder.

Name: maiwand yar
Charges: conspiracy to participate in terrorist activitesterrorist activities
Details: maiwand yar is a former student of mechanical engineering at the university of manitoba. in 2007, it is believed that yar departed canada with accomplice ferid ahmed imam for pakistan. according to witnesses, yar advised that he and imam were going to ally themselves with the taliban and attend a terrorist training camp in order to receive instruction on firearms, explosives and guerilla warfare. their specific objective for joining the taliban was to fight and kill nato (north atlantic treaty organization) soldiers in afghanistan. in a letter sent in 2009, yar stated that he had in fact spent time in both the taliban and al qaida.

Name: christian bergstaller
Alias: bergstaller,  christian gerhard /  bergstaller,  christian gehard /  bergstaller,  gehard christian
Details: bergstaller committed multiple frauds at various financial institutions in the lower mainland between july 2017 – december 2017. bergstaller opened various accounts in different names and saturated the accounts with fraudulent cheque deposits and committed fraudulent cash withdrawals. bergstaller is currently wanted canada wide out of vancouver, british columbia.

Name: mohanbhai patel
Details: wanted for the 1999 parental abduction of his child, kashmin patel. believed to be in india.

Name: andrei ejov
Details: on march 2 2004, andrei ejov physically attacked a male victim and beat him with a baseball bat. under the assumption that the victim was dead, ejov placed the lifeless body into a hockey bag, only to realize that he was still alive. ejov removed him from the bag and drove him to a hospital, where the victim later recovered. it is believed that ejov may have fled back to russia. a canada-wide warrant of arrest was issued against ejov for attempted murder and aggravated assault.

Name: jaroslav krumlik
Details: on february 12 1999, the rcmp were made aware of juvenile sexual assaults involving two young male victims that took place in several canadian provinces over a period of time. these assaults started in the winter of 1973 and continued until the fall of 1977. the juvenile victims were sexually assaulted numerous times by an adult male, jaroslav krumlik, a czechoslovakian who resided in the united states and canada.

Name: khadar hassan khalib
Details: wanted for conspiracy, participation in activity of terrorist group and leaving canada to participate in activity of a terrorist group.

Name: liban abdi sheikhadem
Alias: liban abdinassir sheikhadem /  liban abdinassi sheikhadem /  liban abdem nasser sheikhadem /  p a c
Details: on july 31 2011, ottawa police responded to a stabbing in the downtown area. upon arrival, officers and paramedics found a male unconscious and bleeding. the male was rushed to hospital where he was pronounced dead. the investigation led to the identification of liban sheikhadem as the suspect in the crime. sheikhadem has a history of violence and drug possession.

Name: surjid singh presto
Details: surjid singh presto is a first time federal offender serving a life sentence for murder which occurred in june of 1974, as a result of a dispute between he and his landlord.

Name: ken cuong manh nguyen
Alias: nguye,  nken cuon manh /  nguyen,  cuong manh /  nguyen,  cong manh
Details: ken nguyen is currently serving a life sentence for second degree murder of a rival asian gang member in 1999.

Name: mohammad sodagari
Details: mohammed sodagari is wanted on a canada-wide warrant for two counts of sexual assault against a 21 year old female. sodagari was charged in this matter but failed to attend court. he was educated as an engineer in iran and was working in a factory while in canada.

Name: imad ibrahim
Details: wanted for counterfeiting, possession of prohibited weapon, manufacture fraudulent credit cards, use of forged credit cards, possession of credit card data (2 counts), possession of instrument for copying credit card data, possession of instrument for forging or falsifying credit cards, possession of property obtained by crime, forgery, uttering forged documents, possession of identity information with the intent to commit an indictable offence, distribution of identify information with the intent to commit a criminal offence, conspiracy to commit an indictable offence (4 counts), participation in activities of a criminal organization, trafficking in substance- cocaine (2 counts) and possession for purpose of trafficking- cocaine

Name: gioncondo napoli
Details: gioncondo napoli was convicted of trafficking narcotics in 1981. he served federal jail time before being released on parole, at which time he disappeared. gioncondo has family living in italy.

Name: babak ghanad
Details: on july 4 2011, babak ghanad murdered an 18 year old toronto area woman. ghanad then drove to mexico where he boarded a flight to germany, then continued on to tehran, iran. ghanad is a truck driver by trade with no fixed address. he travelled extensively along the east coast from canada to florida, as well as through western canada into california and texas. ghanad spent time in indonesia before coming to canada. police believe he is currently in iran.

Name: fernando lemagueresse
Details: fernando lemagueresse is wanted canada-wide for multiple counts of sexual assault, sexual assault causing bodily harm, sexual interference and sexual exploitation. lemagueresse committed these crimes against his daughter and step daughters over the course of several years of their childhood. he has ties in toronto, montreal and chile. in 2010, lemagueresse attempted to return to canada from chile, but canceled his flight after receiving information that the police were looking for him.

Name: nicolaos kiriopoulos

On October 16, 2023, four inmates, Johnifer Barnwell, Marc Kerry Anderson, Joey Fournier, and Chavis Demaryo Stokes, escaped from the Bibb County Detention Center located at 668 Oglethorpe Street in Macon, Georgia. Barnwell was convicted in federal court on October 2, 2023, he escaped while awaiting sentencing.

Name: DAWN MARIE MOZINO - BRYN MAWR, PENNSYLVANIA
Details: On May 22, 1989, Dawn Marie Mozino was last seen at the bus stop near Bryn Mawr Hospital, where she worked in food services.  Mozino never arrived home after her shift.  Mozino is learning disabled, with a mental capacity of a 13-year-old person.  She was last seen wearing a gray skirt, maroon vest, white shirt, and black bow tie.

Name: JANE DOE - LINN COUNTY, OREGON
Details: On April 3, 2020, the partially skeletonized remains of an adult female were discovered along a dirt road off Santiam Highway (U.S. 20) in the Willamette National Forest, Linn County, Oregon. Cause of death has not been determined, but the estimated time of death is between eight weeks and one year prior to discovery. No personal effects to include jewelry, identification, or cell phone were recovered. Dental records are available for comparison.

Name: GREGORY C. YETMAN
Distinguishing Marks: Yetman has a tattoo on his back between his shoulders.
Caution: Gregory C. Yetman is wanted by the FBI for his alleged involvement in the violence at the United States Capitol on January 6, 2021. A federal arrest warrant was issued for Yetman in the United States District Court, District of Columbia, Washington, D.C., on November 6, 2023, after he was charged with Assaulting, Resisting, or Impeding Certain Officers; Obstruction of Law Enforcement During Civil Disorder; Entering and Remaining in a Restricted Building or Grounds; Engaging in Physical Violence in a Restricted Building or Grounds; and Act of Physical Violence in the Capitol Grounds or Buildings.

Name: AMEERA DEADRICK - HOUSTON, TEXAS
Details: Ameera Deadrick was last seen in a Facebook video on approximately April 1, 2016. It appeared in the video she was at a Chuck E. Cheese, possibly in Houston, Texas. According to Ameera’s biological father, he left Ameera with a family friend named “Tootie” in the vicinity of Hubbard, Texas, on November 14, 2016, which is four hours away from Houston. At the time, Tootie may have been living in an apartment in Waco, Texas.

Name: ELEUTERIO SUAREZ
Alias: Eleuterio Jimenez Suarez, Eleuterio Suarez Jimenez, Eleuteri Suarez
Caution: Eleuterio Suarez is wanted for allegedly raping a 9-year-old girl on multiple occasions in Franklin, Tennessee, in 2011. In December 2014, the Circuit Court for Williamson County in Franklin, Tennessee, issued an arrest warrant for Suarez, after he was charged with five counts of rape of child, three counts of aggravated sexual battery, and solicitation to commit rape of child. A federal arrest warrant was issued for Suarez on September 24, 2015, in the United States District Court for the Middle District of Tennessee, Nashville, Tennessee, after he was charged with unlawful flight to avoid prosecution.
Remarks: SHOULD BE CONSIDERED AN INTERNATIONAL FLIGHT RISK

Name: ALFREDO ANTONIO ARREDONDO
Distinguishing Marks: Arredondo has the following tattoos: the word "Pasillas" on the right side of his chest, the word "Irma" underneath his right elbow, and the words "Never trust them hoes" above his left hip.
Caution:
The FBI's San Francisco Field Office is assisting the Hollister Police Department in California with the search for Alfredo Antonio Arredondo.  Arredondo is wanted for murder in the death of a man on April 5, 2021.  Arredondo is alleged to have shot and killed the victim after the two men had a disagreement at a restaurant in Hollister, California.

 

On June 7, 2021, Arredondo was charged with murder in the Superior Court of California, County of San Benito, and a state warrant was issued for his arrest.
Remarks: SHOULD BE CONSIDERED ARMED AND DANGEROUS AND AN ESCAPE RISK

Name: BRIAN CHRISTOPHER FRANCIS
Distinguishing Marks: Francis has a scar on his face.
Caution: Brian Christopher Francis is wanted for his alleged involvement in the murder of one individual and the attempted murder of a second individual in Hagerstown, Maryland, on the afternoon of July 30, 2023.  Both victims had been shot in an apartment.  On August 2, 2023, Francis was charged in the District Court for Washington County, Maryland, with 13 counts, including murder and attempted murder.  A federal arrest warrant was issued by the United States District Court for the District of Maryland, Baltimore, Maryland, on August 11, 2023, after Francis was charged federally with unlawful flight to avoid prosecution.
Remarks: SHOULD BE CONSIDERED ARMED AND DANGEROUS

Name: MICHAEL SURBER
Charges: Seeking Information, Case of the Week
Details:
On the evening of November 10, 2009, Michael Surber, a nationally renowned pool player, was murdered in his home in Ocean Springs, Mississippi.  It is believed that Surber was playing pool in a bar in Gulfport, Mississippi, earlier that day when he met an unknown White male, seen above.  It is believed that Surber left the bar with this unknown individual and was later found deceased.
 
The unknown individual was described as a White male, possibly between the ages of 55 and 65, approximately 5'8" to 6'0" and 170 to 185 pounds, with a receding hairline and ponytail.  He may have had gray hair, gaps between his teeth, and worn glasses.

Name: SERGIO PEREZ MARTINEZ
Distinguishing Marks: Perez Martinez has a scar on the left side of his face, a tattoo on the back of his neck, a tattoo on his left forearm, and a tattoo on his back.
Caution:
Sergio Perez Martinez is wanted for escaping confinement. On July 11, 2022, Perez Martinez pled guilty in federal court to one count of conspiracy to distribute methamphetamine, and one count of conspiracy to commit money laundering. Martinez was being held in the Cass County Missouri jail and escaped confinement on December 5, 2022.

 

On December 7, 2022, Sergio Perez Martinez was charged via federal criminal complaint in the United States District Court, Western District of Missouri, Kansas City, Missouri, with Escape from Confinement and Aid or Assist Escape from Confinement.
Remarks: SHOULD BE CONSIDERED ARMED AND DANGEROUS

Name: DOUBLE HOMICIDE INVESTIGATION
Details:
The Federal Bureau of Investigation, along with Fauquier County Sheriff’s Office, is seeking the public's assistance in identifying the unknown individual(s) responsible for the murder of Duong Nguyen and his son, America Nguyen, in Bealeton, Virginia.
 
Sometime between the evening of November 7, 2018, and the morning of November 8, 2018, Duong, age 61, and America, age 22, were shot in the middle of the night by an unknown assailant(s) while in their home located in Bealeton, Virginia. The Nguyens were unarmed.  Anyone who may have traveled the Rt. 28, Catlett Road, corridor in Fauquier County to Prince William County, on the evening of November 7, 2018, or the early morning of November 8, 2018, is asked to contact the FBI if you remember anything or anyone suspicious during your commute.

Name: CATHERINE BARBARA DAVIDSON
Details: The FBI's Detroit Field Office and Michigan State Police are seeking the public's assistance in locating Catherine Davidson. On September 1, 1973, six-year-old Catherine Davidson was reported missing at Warren Dunes State Park in Sawyer, Michigan. It is believed that her possible death occurred in the Chicago, Illinois, area around the same time period.

On October 16, 2023, Anderson was charged with escape (felony) in the Bibb County Magistrate Court, Bibb County, Georgia, and a state warrant was issued for his arrest.
